properties.sfomuseum:airline: Pan American Airways  (Pan American World Airways)
properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, Pan American Airways, eastbound from Manila to San Francisco, March 12-April 4, 1936; identified by donor with additional information: "The Philippine Clipper was scheduled to depart Manila, March 9, 1936. However, it had blown an engine and a replacement had to be flown out. Thus mail departed on the return flight of the China Clipper, March 29, 1936, arriving in San Francisco, April 4, 1936";a. cover: multicolored cachet with illustration of Clipper in flight over ship at sail and route map with text, "Philippine Clipper's flight, Manila - San Francisco, via airmail"; four postmarks on front: March 12, 1936 in Manila, P.I. with football-shaped “2” cancellation marks over twelve red 10-centavos stamps; addressed to Mr. D.C. Stanion; stamped, "Air Mail" over lower edge of cachet on front.Note: received on .156 b. information sheet: 8 1/2 x 11 with black text; additional information prepared by donor; flight cover was received mounted to sheet with photo corners with item .156 a mounted on same sheet.
properties.wof:name: airmail flight cover: Pan American Airways, Eastbound from Manila to San Francisco, March 12-April 4, 1936
